<h2 align="center" id="-key-features">âœ¨ Key Features</h2>

### ğŸ® Simulation & Attacks

- **Swarm Simulation** â€” Dynamic graph-based UAV network modeling with configurable parameters
- **Attack Injection** â€” Multiple spoofing scenarios with ground truth tracking

### âš”ï¸ Attack Types

| Attack Type                   | Description                                               |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ­ **Phantom UAV Injection**  | Non-existent UAVs broadcasting fake Remote ID messages    |
| ğŸ“ **Position Falsification** | Legitimate UAVs reporting spoofed GPS coordinates         |
| ğŸ”€ **Coordinated Attacks**    | Multiple synchronized spoofers disrupting swarm consensus |

### ğŸ” Detection Methods

| Method                   | Description                             | Performance                 |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| ğŸ“Š **Spectral Analysis** | Laplacian eigenvalue anomaly detection  | Fast & lightweight          |
| ğŸ¯ **Centrality-Based**  | Graph centrality metric analysis        | Good for structural changes |
| ğŸ¤– **Machine Learning**  | Node2Vec embeddings + Isolation Forests | Adaptive detection          |
| ğŸ” **Cryptographic**     | Ed25519 signature verification          | **100% TPR, 0% FPR!**       |

### ğŸ“ˆ Analysis & Visualization

- **Consensus Analysis** â€” Quantify attack impact on swarm coordination
- **Publication-Quality Plots** â€” ROC curves, heatmaps, comparisons (300 DPI PDF+PNG)
- **Live Real-Time Animation** â€” Watch UAVs move and attacks unfold with PySide6 (Qt6)
- **Interactive Detection Overlay** â€” Enhanced visualization with detection status

